HWRT's Compliance Policy

It is HWRT's policy to adhere to all applicable federal, state and local rules and regulations. The owners and management of this facility regard employee and public safety as a very serious matter and have taken many precautions to maintain a safe working and public environment.  Some of these precautions include:

¿	Preparing and implementing a Facility Response Plan (FRP);
¿	Complying with NFPA 58 Liquefied Petroleum Gas Code
¿	Annual inspections of the butane system by a qualified outside contractor;
¿	Preparing and implementing a Spill, Prevention, Control and Countermeasure (SPCC) Plan;
¿	Instituting safe operating procedures;
¿	Training employees in safety programs and procedures; and
¿	Coordinating with the Local Emergency Planning Committee (LEPC).

Accident Prevention 

Employees are trained to recognize the hazards of the process and all changes to the process are reviewed to ensure that the safety, health, and environmental consequences of the change are addressed prior to making the change. Routine daily, monthly, and annual inspection are conducted to ensure compliance with existing safety policies. The facility has a strong commitment to the safe handling of butane and other flammable materials and to minimize the probability of an accidental release.  This is achieved through a combination of safety equipment, personnel training and operating procedures.  The safety equipment includes excess flow valves, pressure relief valves and emergency shut off valves.  Annual inspections of the Butane system are performed by an experienced, knowledgeable, outside contractor. The condition of the tank, piping, and supports, checking the internal valves, pressure relief valves, emergency shut-off valves and cables, pressure gauge, and liquid pump are key features of th
